<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1227" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1227">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/2082</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The German Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                            <gloss type="to">
                                <hi rend="italic">Counselor for the Department of State</hi>
                            </gloss>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. A 2433]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-02">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 3</hi>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: On account of the great
                            importance of the principles involved, I should be very much obliged to
                            you for an official note giving the reasons why the Government of the
                            United States withheld permission for the <hi rend="italic">Pisa</hi> to
                            clear from the harbor of New York, so that I can inform my Government
                            without making any mistake. Personally I fail to see how this decision
                            can be brought in accordance with the Hague convention.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Bernstorff</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>